AFTER being
sworn-in last week, president Cyril Ramaphosa has managed to negotiate with the
Chamber of Mines to postpone its court application on reviewing the Mining
Charter.The
Presidency said on Sunday that it had been in discussion with the Chamber of
Mines to resolve the deadlock over the mining charter.According
to The Presidency, this was done in a bid to facilitate a process of developing
