of Mines agreed jointly with the Department of Mineral Resources to postpone
its court application which was due to be heard in the High Court from today.“The
postponement serves to allow parties the space to engage and find an amicable
solution,” said the Presidency.On Friday,
President Cyril Ramaphosa committed to intensifying engagements with all
stakeholders on the Mining Charter.“I am
certain we will be able to resolve the current deadlock and agree on a Charter
that both accelerates transformation and grows this vital sector of our
economy,” President Ramaphosa said.